302570497.name: XY
302570497.description: Kalos has been revealed, yet so much still remains unseen! New Trainers, new tactics, and the awe-inspiring Xerneas and Yveltal await—as does something else. Something…different. Something to make even the mightiest of Pokémon-EX tremble! A new age begins in the Pokémon TCG with Mega Evolution!

302570498.name: XY
302570498.description: Kalos has been revealed, yet so much still remains unseen! New Trainers, new tactics, and the awe-inspiring Xerneas and Yveltal await—as does something else. Something…different. Something to make even the mightiest of Pokémon-EX tremble! A new age begins in the Pokémon TCG with Mega Evolution!

BasicBlueClassicPCD.name: Hidden Depths
BasicBlueClassicPCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Articuno, Gyarados, Lapras
Chill your opponent to the bone with this Water-type deck! Articuno can find Energy and then let loose a Freezing Wind attack. Gyarados can hit the opposing Pokémon hard and weaken every other Pokémon in play with a Berserker Splash. Lapras helps out by fetching from your deck the exact Trainer card you need! Add some awesome Trainer and Energy cards like Max Revive and Splash Energy to keep your deck strong for the long battle, and this deck displays the hidden power of the deeps!

BasicRedClassicPCD.name: Born of Fire
BasicRedClassicPCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Moltres, Ninetales, Arcanine
Burn it up with this Fire-type deck! Arcanine and Rapidash have big attacks that discard Energy—attach a Burning Energy so it comes right back, or use an Energy Retrieval Trainer card. Moltres is a giant Basic Pokémon that can deliver huge damage at the cost of hitting itself. And when Ninetales attacks with Flickering Flames, the hypnotic effect leaves your opponent's Pokémon Asleep. With Trainer cards like Scorched Earth and Professor Sycamore to keep your hand fired up, you can really bring on the heat!

BasicYellowClassicPCD.name: Crushing Current
BasicYellowClassicPCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Zapdos, Raichu, Kangaskhan
This Lightning-type deck is a rolling slugfest! Kangaskhan brings the big hits while Zapdos unleashes its Raging Thunder. Raticate can leave your opponent's Pokémon Poisoned, but they can't return the favor because it's immune to Special Conditions. With an extra-full Bench thanks to the Sky Field Stadium card, Raichu's Circle Circuit attack can hit for tons of damage! Finally, Trainer cards like Potion and Pokémon Fan Club can keep you in the game, and Double Colorless Energy can power up your Pokémon fast!

XY1DestructionRushBundle.name: Destruction Rush
XY1DestructionRushBundle.description:
A Swift Strike of Darkness! 
Leave your opponents in the dust with the Destruction Rush theme deck! Yveltal retrieves lost Energy for a quick recovery with Oblivion Wing and wields the devastating Darkness Blade to great effect. Krookodile can Knock Back a battle-ready Pokémon to the Bench and keep powerful Supporter cards out of play. With Malamar's Mental Panic to keep your opponent's attacks at bay, retaliation won't be easy—and the rush to destruction will be complete!

XY1ResilientLifeBundle.name: Resilient Life
XY1ResilientLifeBundle.description:
A Strong Shield of Energy! 
Resist, refuel, and retaliate with the Resilient Life theme deck! Xerneas can find Fairy Energy to recharge your Benched Pokémon, and Aromatisse moves that Energy around to wherever you need it most. Once your Pokémon have Fairy Energy attached, things get even better: Slurpuff's Sweet Veil Ability protects them from Special Conditions, and the Fairy Garden Stadium card lets them retreat for free! Flexible defenses are the key to your victory!
